          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GLASD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Two Glass Solid State Nuclear Track Detectors",
                "Were Used. The Detectors were Made of Soda Lime Glasses",
                "Having Uranium As an Impurity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "EDEG",
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "On the Surface of the Glass Detectors Plastic Energy",
                "Degraders were Fixed. The Energy Degradiation For these",
                "Plastics was Accurately Known. After Irradiation the",
                "Glasses are Etched in 4.8% Hydrofluoric Acid For 1 Min",
                "At 22 Degrees.  Tracks are Counted Under Different",
                "Sections of the Surface Representing Different Regions",
                "Of He-3 Energy As Defined by the Energy Degrading",
                "Echelon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "No Error Analysis Nor Error Values are Given."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Above 28 MeV the Contribution to the Fission Cross",
                "Section Could Come from Anyone or All of the Following",
                "Processes- U(HE-3,F), U(HE-3,NF), U(HE-3,PF) Or",
                "U(HE-3,DF). This is Due to the Fact That Above the",
                "Coulomb Barrier There is a Great Probability of Direct",
                "Interaction Between He-3 and Uranium."
              ]
            }
          ],
